Create, update, and delete persist the in-flight
OCI work request in `status.async.current`,
normalize Delegate Access Control
`OperationStatus*` values into shared async
classes, and normalize work-request
`OperationType*` values into
create/update/delete phases before deriving
conditions and requeue behavior.
Create prefers the returned `DelegationControl`
body when OCI exposes an identifier and
otherwise recovers the OCID from work-request
resources before polling `GetDelegationControl`.
Update also gates completion on a succeeded work
request plus a readable `GetDelegationControl`.
Only `displayName`, `description`,
`numApprovalsRequired`,
`delegationSubscriptionIds`,
`isAutoApproveDuringMaintenance`, `resourceIds`,
`preApprovedServiceProviderActionNames`,
`notificationTopicId`,
`notificationMessageFormat`, `freeformTags`, and
`definedTags` reconcile in place.
`compartmentId`, `resourceType`, `vaultId`, and
`vaultKeyId` remain replacement-only drift, so
the published runtime never exercises
provider-only
`ChangeDelegationControlCompartment`.
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats `FAILED` and
`NEEDS_ATTENTION` as terminal failure without
requeue, and delete retains the finalizer until
`GetDelegationControl` or fallback
`ListDelegationControls` confirms the resource
is deleted or not found.
